<span class="displaytext">the (candidate full) presidential committee announced today that mario bruno, jr. has joined the team as executive director for the state of new york. <p>bruno, who served in the former mayor's administration, will oversee all aspects of the (candidate last) campaign in the state, from building upon existing grassroots support to promoting rudy's message of strong leadership. </p><p>"mario is well-respected in (PARTY NAME) circles," said (candidate last) campaign manager michael duhaime. "his experience as a public servant and his political knowledge are tremendous assets as we work toward victory in the primary. mayor (candidate last) is proud to have mario on board." </p><p>bruno joins a strong and growing new york leadership team including senate majority leader joseph l. bruno, assembly (PARTY NAME) leader jim tedisco and (PARTY NAME) state committee chairman joseph mondello, who have all endorsed rudy. former congressman guy molinari and former new york state (PARTY NAME) committee chairman bill powers are serving as state co-chairs. in addition, rudy has received endorsements from over fifty current and former members of the state senate and state assembly and more than fifty (PARTY NAME) county chairmen and county executives. </p><p><strong><u>about mario bruno, jr.:</u></strong> </p><p>a lifelong new yorker, mario served as assistant commissioner of the new york city department of youth and community development and was originally appointed by mayor (candidate last). </p><p>mario, a mechanical engineer by training, holds a bachelor's degree from the polytechnic institute of new york. he held various roles within the new york city department of transportation for 19 years. mario is active in (PARTY NAME) politics, having managed senator (candidate full)'s new york presidential campaign in 2000. he served as a member of the new york (PARTY NAME) state committee for five years and has managed several local races. mario lives on staten island.</p></span>



